description: While Demon Fox holds the Blood Syndicate in its clutches, the newest Syndicate member Kwai makes her presence known!
name: Demon Shade
The Moment of Truth
Louder Than A Bomb, Chapter Two: War at 30 Frames per Second

volume.name: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles/Flaming Carrot Crossover

name: Cultural Trade

volume.name: Buck Godot - Zap Gun For Hire

description:
Blood of Ten Chiefs 3 and 4 are devoted to the telling of Graywolf and Swiftspear's private hunting. It tells the tale of how Swiftspear became Two-Spear.
Chronologically, the then Wolfriders were polarized into a few tribemates who were nearly divine The High-Ones , and a few like Graywolf who had animal-wolf tendencies. Swiftspear's wolf is murdered by human villagers, who cut of its ears but do not take the meat. Swiftspear is outraged and seeks vengence, bringing Graywolf who must rescue him when a failed confrontation ensues.
This is an incident that would lead to the developing of a near-permanent feud between elves and human on the world of two moons.
name: Swift-Spear

description:
This is the Revelation of Rayek's childhood in Sorrow's End. He rejected the ways of his father and learned to enjoy the taste of meat.
He trapped and hunted the species of the native desert and brought home his catch. While he spend his afternoons in solitude as a hunter, he discovered some of his divine talents, which was the power of the light within his eyes to paralyze low-minded creatures. Rayek transfers under Savah's mentorship.
name: THE ENEMY'S FACE

description:
The Go-Backs, led by Chot, decide to sneak through the cave-system to Sun Village and steal the statue-Palace of The High-Ones. Yun cuts Kahvi and Tyldak free from the web that they were stuck in since they tried to steal the palace.

A volcano erupts nearby.
name: WAR PART ONE

description:
The United Nations has invaded Monster Island under the orders of Senator Munson. The leader, Capt. Sylvester Hammer is met by the Mole Man. The captain tries to tell the Mole Man that this is no longer his island. But Mole Man responds by awakening one of the giant monsters that give the island it's name.

The troops have brought weaponry ready for the Infinity Watch, but not something as large as what they face now. Mole Man then unleashes an army of Moloids armed with clubs. Mole Man brings the men back to their ship after he has clothes his Moloids with their uniforms.

Meanwhile, Warlock has traveled to the Goddess' subconscious and tries to bend the Goddess' will with his own spirit. She proves too powerful, her power augmented by the Cosmic Egg.

Mole Man arrives back on sure and he and the Moloids notice the Sun is growing bigger. It soon engulfs them, having gone nova.
name: Siege!

description: In "Sanctum," Batman's battle with a deranged killer in an old Gotham City graveyard leads to the shattering of an ancient crypt and the unleashing of an incredible supernatural force that threatens to consume the Dark Knight's sanity, his life...and his very soul!
name: Sanctum

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
1. Po Part 1 (text)
Victor signs a book contract with the Vertigo Horse publishing company and starts a new book about women.

2. Po Part 2 (comic)
Po tells Astoria, Cerebus and Cirin that he brought them together. Elsewhere, Swoon appears.

3. Address to UK retailers 9/17/93 (ful text message)
name: Mothers and Daughters 26 : Po

description:
In Colorado, Archangel and Jean Grey encounter a mysteriously-revived Candy Southern and Archangel's nemesis Cameron Hodge!

Angel and Jean Grey return to his old home to discover two shocking surprises. Candy Southern and Cameron Hodge. But both were supposed to be dead. Unfortunately Hodge tries to kill everyone and Candy sacrifices herself to stop him.
name: Mortal Coils

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: The X-Men are attempting to return home on a near destroyed Black Bird after a battle with Magneto. Also, Professor X and Jean Grey try to keep Wolverine alive after his adamantium skeleton was ripped out by Magneto. The X-Men finally return safely home and Wolverine is slowly recovering. Later, Wolverine trains in the Danger Room and finds out that he was born with bone claws. The next day Wolverine leaves the X-Men because he now longer feels fit for the team.
name: Fatal Attractions Part 5: Nightmares Persist

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Fifty years ago, Louis Sendak was a mystical adventurer called Scarab, possessor of a magical amulet that transformed him into one of the strangest, most powerful heroes of the Golden Age. Now he's back - with a second chance at life, youth and redemption. Louis's life lost all meaning on the day his wife, Eleanor, was drawn through a mystical portal into a strange realm called the Labyrinth. For years, Louis tried in vain to force open the door, but it remained sealed despite his great power. Despondent, he abandoned his life as Scarab. But when the supernatural assassin called the Sicari opens the way to the Labyrinth, Louis realizes he can rescue Eleanor, and in the process, finds a reason to live. All he must do is fight his way past a murderer, reclaim a mysterious and unpredictable magical power, and come to grips with guilt that has paralyzed him for decades. And that's just the beginning of the horrors that will face him in his new life.
name: All Roads Lead to the Minotaur
Family Matters

description: Arms dealer Griff makes war his job but none of his business! That is, until he's an innocent bystander during an assassination attempt and shot down with his own product. Will Griff develop a conscience? You'll be surprised at the answer.

The one true Man of Steel is back in action in Metropolis! And so is the creature known as Bloodthirst...and this time he intends to suck Metropolis dry unless Superman can stop him.

Notes:

  • Triangle 1993 #33.
  • Chronological continuation from Action Comics #692.
  • Chronological continuation in Superman #83.
name: Bad Character

description:
Now the guest of the ruler of Santa Prisca, Catwoman must play bodyguard as hired assassins and a familiar face attempt to overthrow the dictator.

Catwoman is now under the protection of Jefe Del Pais for saving his life from Guillermo, a hired assassin.

Later, the treachery unfolds as the events will expose a new foe and enlighten new facts about who really was behind the hit on Selena. The men of honor will reveal themselves not to be who they seem...
name: Life Lines, Chapter Four: Full Circle

description:
Spider-Man's on trial! But what’s his crime? The cybernetic Jury has captured Spidey and is holding him responsible for the release of Venom’s symbiote! Aunt May confirms her suspicions about Peter’s parents.

In the first of a three-part series, Mr. Taylor recruits Sentry and the Jury to bring in Spider-Man. Upon his capture, he intends to trial Spidey for the crime of bringing Venom's alien costume to Earth, a crime punishable by death!
name: Trial By Jury - Part 1: Judgement Night

description: Part 3 of 3. Time is running out for Picard as a holodeck scenario gone awry threatens to destroy Worf and Troi.
name: Hidden Agendas

description:
With Rayek's triumphant return, Cutter has the opportunity to vent his rage for abandoning him on the World of Two Moons for thousands of years while Rayek pursued the mysteries of the universe in the spaceship known as the Palace of The High-Ones.
Picknose's underground troll clan becomes the welcome scene of a wrestling match between the two warriors. Rayek and Cutter deliver several brutal blows to each other, but the fight is until the death, and no healers were allowed to intervene unless one of the fighters gives up. Cutter gains the upper hand and subdues Rayek, who withstands much abuse but doesnot forfeit. In the end, while nearly dead, Rayek only thanks Cutter for raising his daughter Venka.
name: ROGUE'S CHALLENGE

description:
In England, as Batman, Bruce enlisted the services of a local vigilante named Hood. Dr. Kinsolving's kidnapper, Benedict Asp, began testing her healing powers. He was able to amplify and reverse the healing, causing death. Hood delivered the info on Asp. Wayne continued therapy.

Notes:

  • Continued from Justice League Task Force #6.
name: Bruce Wayne - Part One: The Hood

description:
This extra-sized issue has it all: a wedding, a death, a rebirth, changes in the Legion lineup, and the explosive return of a long-missing Legionnaire!

As Jan Arrah prepares to embrace death, he sees the wedding, recoveries, arrivals, and departures of several Legionnaires.

Overview

Gloria infiltrates the New Orleans Grendel clan, presided over by the deadly Renute, and discovers that some very bad juju is afoot. Meanwhile, deep in the Louisiana bayou, Mantovani and Calhoun are hot on the trail of the mysterious child who holds the key to the Batiaque slayings -- only to find Renute's men lying in wait. As if that weren't enough, the fourth Grendel, Bixby, goes on a lunatic rampage, slaughtering everything in his path!

Summary

Gloria watched a voodoo rite, and becomes more and more disillusioned with the New Orleans Grendel Krewe. She sets her sights on Renute as the man who controls the treasure she seeks. She continues to manipulate Radley in order to get information from him.

Renute himself has his eyes on all four of the Grendels who have become active in his city, hoping they do not ruin his plans to become the reincarnation of Hunter Rose.

Bixby, meanwhile, is killing everyone he meets, thinking they are trolls.

Calhoun and Mantovani search the swamps for Simone, Calhoun's lost love (and Bixby's as well). They find her--now a vampire--at the same time as some of Renute's Grendel soldiers. They all fight, and Renute's men and Simone are all killed. Her unnamed young son survives. We discover that Mantovani has a silver bionic hand.
name: One Rite, Three Wrongs

volume.name: Grendel Tales: Four Devils, One Hell

description:
Grimbor the Chainsman returns for an attack against the water world of Quarantine...and Kent Shakespeare, Celeste and Ivy return to action.

Grimbor has come to Quarantine to fetch his daughter, leaving Neon and Impulse to fend him off with several Legion tykes.
name: A L'il Legion Adventure

description: Archer & Armstrong head to the beaches of sunny Florida in a bid to locate Armstrong's lost art collection! But as the duo head underwater in search of the missing possessions, they might find something a little more threatening than buried treasure. Oh, and Armstrong wrestles an alligator in this issue. So there.
name: Alligator

description:
At last, Project Rising Spirit has successfully repeated the Bloodshot procedure. But who is on the receiving end of the nanite transfusion this time and what is his connection to the original Bloodshot? The answers lie in Rising Spirit's Japanese headquarters where Michael Lazarus goes toe-to-toe with Bloodshot 2.0!

Death of Mr. Iwatsu.
name: Empirical Dynasty

description: Master Darque is scouring the Earth for relics of necromantic power-- the thirty pieces of silver the Romans paid Judas. If he and his servitor, an elemental of corrupted Earth, gathers them all before Gilad can stop them, it will spell the end for the line of the Geomancers forever!
name: Blood Money

description: Travel through ages of conflict, from the bloody fields of Gallipoli to medieval Rome and the shores of pagan England, as the Eternal Warrior, attacked in the modern day by a priest with a mysterious vendetta, re-lives his history of violence.
name: Fair Arms, Just Intents

description: When Flatline is taken hostage, the H.A.R.D. Corps team attempts a daring rescue. As rising tensions within the team come to a head, a team member falls in action.
name: The Body Farm

description: Peter Stanchek's home has been burned to the ground! And, meanwhile, secret attackers are taking down his friends one by one. But as Peter begins a frantic manhunt to apprehend those responsible, will he be walking right into a death trap set by none other than Toyo Harada?
name: Twilight Of The Eighth Day - Part Two: Dead End

description: When they learn that the Malevs’ plan is to destroy the forests which would destroy Earth’s air recycling plants and enable the Malevs to poison the atmosphere and make the planet uninhabitable for humans, Magnus and company try to stop that plan and find help in the Rain Forest in “The Battle for South Am Part Four – Allies.”
name: The Battle For South Am - Chapter Four: Allies

description: Something seems amiss as Rai and the Future Force investigate the Malev's plan. Could the Malev's plot be even worse than our heroes had anticipated?
name: The Battle For South Am-- Chapter Three: Targets

description:
Pursued by Master Darque and an army of the undead, Dr. Mirage and his wife flee through the snowy slopes of Tibet. Slowly, Dr. Mirage realizes the nature of his new ghostly form, all the while seeking a way to defeat the rage of Darque.

It's fight or flight as the villain who made Doctor Mirage his ghostly self decides to clear up any loose ends.
name: Darque Passage - Part 2

volume.name: The Second Life of Doctor Mirage

description: Stronghold grows to monstrous proportions after being "slipped a mickey" on date night. Unable to control his powers, will his atoms collapse and devastate half the Eastern Seaboard?
name: Mass Hysteria

description:
Turok is captured and brought to the lair of Dr. Noel, a collector of rare life forms.

Picking up from last issue Turok, Andy Howell and Regan Howell have been already captured by Longhunter. Longhunter then delivers them to Dr. Noel but not before Turok makes his mark on Longhunters face. Dr. Noel plans on keeping Turok as he is a collector of rare species and Turok is a man out of time. Noel considers his a one of a kind specimen.

Before being lock up Turok and the others find out that Dr. Noel has Allosaurus' in his menagerie and they are sick. In their cells the three escape thank to the skills of Andy. the escape is closely monitored by Longhunter and leads to the confrontation on the cover. after the battle Turok goes back in to deal with Dr. Noel. Dr. Noel in fear backs up falling to his death in the allosaurus pet and ominously leaving his psychotic son with the menagerie.
name: Shades Of Yesterday Part 3:The Collection

description:
Aric's escape from civilization takes a surprising turn for the worse! With his adopted village as the target of a much larger conspiracy, Aric must once again rise as a protector of the innocent. But without the X-O Manowar armor's protection, can Aric ever be the hero he once was? It's metal vs. mettle as Aric's true strength is finally tested!

Randy Cartier in X-O Armor.
name: White Kings And Black Knights - Part 2

description: Samuree and Jeri-Ann continue their fight against the hordes of Ariman who have taken over a mid-town apartment building and made it into a battleground. Jeri-Ann's father continues to try and sacrifice her and bring Ariman back to our world, and Samuree is battling the priestess Vanaya.

Tune in this month as Nicole Hollander's "Sylvia" turns to mystery writing; Jean-Michel Charlier and Moebius' rough-n-tough cowboy, Blueberry, continues a run of bad luck; and Andreas' Rork finds the underground action heating up fast in "Rork: Capricorn." Phil Elliott expounds another "Conspiracy Theory," and "Caricatures," by Tom McWeeney returns for another bodacious sketching session. Watch for your letters in another installment of "Black Mail." Painted cover by John Bolton.

Story Titles

  • Sylvia
  • Rork: Capricorn Chapter 3
  • Conspiracy Theory
  • Blueberry: Arizona Love Chapter 4
  • Caricatures $1.00

Overview

It's finally time for some honest-to-goodness "Star Wars," as Luke Skywalker and Vrad Dodonna head for a climactic showdown in space with Darth Vader. Meanwhile, the rest of the Rebel alliance struggles against time to evacuate Yavin Base for their new home on Hoth, as Darth Vader and the Imperial forces plan for a major strike on the Rebel moon. Luke, however, suspects that Vrad is a traitor to the Rebel cause, which leads to an exciting confrontation -- as well as a startling turn of events for one of our Rebel heroes.
name: Doom Mission (part 2)

description:
This issue: the premiere of comics legend Arthur Adams' Monkeyman and O'Brien! Super-smart gorilla, super-strong woman, lots of creepy monsters! Plus, Chris Moeller's tale of conquest continues in this issue with Shadow Empires: "Passages," part 2. Khazar's decision to follow his conscience has left him with only one possible escape route -- out of the chapel and straight through the gates of Hell itself. Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid continues in this issue, with a solid taste of the mayhem incarnate when... someone... starts mucking about in the Patterns of Fate. One wins, one dies. Or is it one dies, one wins? There's still time to place your bets!

Chapters

  • Monkeyman & O'Brien - "Tortorus"
  • Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid - Part 5, "The Greenishness of Money."
  • Shadow Empires: The Passage - Part 2
name: Monkeyman & O'Brien; Hermes vs. The Eyeball Kid; Shadow Empires

description:
A monster is haunting the sewers of New York City, lacerating and burning its victims with impunity. The police are certain they'll solve the mystery, but when two patrolmen are killed by the fire-breathing threat, their confidence is shaken! This supernatural killer seems all but unstoppable!

Who can the city turn to? The lady evangelist in town to pour oil on troubled waters? The mayor, hosting the navies of the world for a peace conference? The police? When battling a mysterious villain, depend on a mysterious hero -- The Shadow!

volume.name: The Shadow: In the Coils of Leviathan

description:
The all-new and improved Bloodsport hits Metropolis with a secret agenda!

A homicidal racist with teleportation powers uses his weapons to murder his way through the city.

Notes:

  • Adam Grant and Bloodsport (DuBois) cameo flashback appearances.
  • On page 6 panel 3 Clark Kent has a Batman coffee cup filled with pencils and pens on his desk.
  • Triangle 1993 #39.
  • Chronological continuation from Superman #84.
  • Chronological continuation in Action Comics #694.
name: Spilled Blood, Skin Game

description: When Animal Man pursues mysterious creatures into the wilderness, he encounters a group of kindred spirits and undergoes a subtle transformation that gives him new insight into the uneasy relationship between humanity and nature. Also, Maxine's odd behavior draws unwanted attention.
name: Communion

description:
AQUAMAN: TIME AND TIDE begins with Aquaman's first encounter with surface world super-beings as the villainous Trickster commits a heist on the high seas. With the Flash (Barry Allen) in hot pursuit, their high-speed battle draws the attention of Aquaman, leading to the Sea King's own confrontation with Trickster.

Synopsis

The issue starts out with a little girl crying about having her goldfish named Goldie flushed down the toilet. Her mom promises her a kitten if she takes it easy on her and she confirms the little girl's thoughts about the toilet being a gateway to “fish heaven”. The dead fish floats through the sanitation department out into the ocean were it is eaten by a bigger fish. The fish swims around and enters a cave were Aquaman is reading and writing in the “Atlantis Chronicles." Over Aquaman's shoulder are images of Aqualad, Mera and Arther Jr. (Aquababy) on the wall. Vulko's image can also be seen in a frame on a ledge used as a table. Aquaman writes about what he knows of his lineage and the first time he was called a hero. This is where the comic tells the story of that time.

The story starts out with Trickster robbing a rich ocean liner. And making his escape running several feet above the water. Barry Allen (The Flash) is running after him on the surface of the water when Aquaman pops out of the water. Flash quickly runs around him and turns his head to see who he almost ran over. This gives Trickster the distraction he needs to toss a slinky at Flash's legs causing him to fall and skim over the water into the side of a shark. He then starts to sink into the ocean. Aquaman saves him from getting eaten by some easily distracted sharks and takes Flash to a subterranean cave.

When Flash regains consciousness Flash talks Aquaman into stopping the Trickster. Aquaman is suspicious but becomes convinced. They quickly find Trickster in a mini-sub and capture him with the help of some killer whales. After Trickster's capture Flash talks Aquaman into coming with him so the people of Crescent Shore can thank him for his heroics.

Aquaman is given the key to the city by the Mayer. Photographers start to take shots of them but they are so bright that they irritate Aquaman's eyes and Flash has to ask them to stop. It is at this point that Aquaman finds out that Trickster has already escaped. He leaves Aquaman with the Mayor who gets Aquaman in his limousine with Jack Shipp and Bart Saxton who are the Mayor's P.R. Staff. They want to make Crescent Shore a superhero city like Metropolis, Gotham and Central City. They have all sorts of merchandise that says Ocean King. They were hoping to change Aquaman's name to Ocean King and have him become the hero of the city. They even have a concept idea for a costume. This annoys Aquaman, but not as much as the smoke from Jack's cigar. He asks for something to drink and is given Vodka. Aquaman thought it was water and gets very upset about the whole thing. He becomes so enraged that he kicks the door off the limo while it is moving and jumps into the path of a semi-truck.

Aquaman avoids the semi and falls to the street were he is swarmed by fans. Aquaman yells at them to get away and as he breaks through the crowd he sees the Trickster. His scuffle with the crowd has left Aquaman's clothes torn and with blood seeping out of his mouth and nose. Fed up with the whole thing he just leaves. This ticks off the Trickster who uses a couple of gimmicks to make Aquaman turn and fight. Aquaman just keeps walking until Trickster becomes so bold as to walk right behind Aquaman and yell in his ear. With one punch Aquaman turns and knocks out Trickster. The crowd goes nuts and talks about how cool Aquaman was in the way he tricked the Trickster. Aquaman turns and tells them that he fully intended to leave them to the Trickster and only stopped Trickster when he got on his nerves. As he walks away a kid looks at a piece of his shirt and wonder out loud if it will be worth anything. Another guy says no he just splashes around and he's no big deal.

When Aquaman reaches the dock he is stopped by the Flash who apologizes for what happened. He then hands Aquaman the king of the city. Flash tells him he is one “hell of a guy”.
name: Flash Back: Time & Tide, part 1

description: Azrael has broken with Robin and is now closing in on his target, but what's most surprising is the unexpected ally the Dark Knight finds in Mayor Krol.
name: Phoenix in Chaos

description: Commissioner Gordon has 24 hours to find an undercover cop who has been caught by mobster Rupert Thorne.
name: Badge of Honor

description: Ignorance is bliss, or so Sherilyn suspects when a man named Nick tells her the strange and prophetic tale about his encounter with the Black Orchid.
name: Acts of Faith

description: BLOODLINES, DC's 1993 Annuals event, reaches its pulse-pounding grand finale in BLOODBATH, a 2-part miniseries (continued from Legion (1989) Annual #4) that draws together most of the world's heroes for the final battle against the deadly alien parasites. The one, true Superman joins the fight, along with the new Batman, as the parasites' savage attacks become a worldwide emergency. A strike force of heroes takes the struggle to the huge, long-hidden home of the parasites...a battle that culminates in the rise of the gargantuan parasite offspring known as the Taker. Concludes in Bloodbath (1993) #2.
name: Bloodbath (Part 1)

description: The Head sleeps and dreams of Window Men, Doctor Void, the Confusers and the infrequently visited corners of Niles Caulder's soul.
name: The Dream Patrol: Return of the Windowmen

description: While Linda Park investigates Razer's employers, Flash tries to take Razer down in "Cut and Run". Part 2 of 2, continued from the previous issue.
name: Cut and Run

description:
As Jade and Obsidian, children of the Golden Age Green Lantern, come to terms with their father's de-aging, Torquemada - sole magic user of the Green Lantern Corps has need of the wielder of the Starheart!

"Ashes to Ashes" - First appearance and origin of the Green Lantern Ash, of Space Sector 650. The story chronicles his wife's murder at the hands of alien vampires and his subsequent hunt for revenge.

"Triumph of the Will" - The story of the corruption and fall of Ayria, the Green Lantern of Aegri Somnia One.

"Green Hell" - The sad tale of Barin, a young Corpsman who fell into a coma from wounds sustained in battle and became the gatekeeper of his own version of Hell.
name: Ashes to Ashes / Triumph of the Will / Green Hell

description: Wonder Woman guest-stars! Trapped in Hawkwoman's body, Hawkman is helpless as Count Viper - having usurped Katar Hol's own body - launches his plan to remake the United States. And his starting point is to take over the minds of Justice League heroes to destroy the man whose body he possesses.
name: The Return of Hawkwoman

description: "Damnation's Flame" Part 1. Needing a bit of a sabbatical after his bottom-of-the-bottle months, Constantine decides to visit New York City--but in his journey learns the danger of falling prey to old enemies.
name: Damnation's Flame, Part One: Brave New World

description:
In an unlikely change of events, Hex is now forced to fight alongside Doc "Cross" Williams, the undead Wild Bill Hickok and several retired army soldiers against a raiding party of violent Chiricahua Apaches. Hex befriends one of the soldiers and the two stage their own retreat firing at advancing Apaches.

But as day turns into night, the soldier begins to succumb to the infection that had set in from an Apache's arrow. Unwilling to become a play toy of the Chiricahua, the soldier takes his own life. Taking the Sarge's horse, Hex doubles back towards the initial battle scene.

He finds that Doc Williams has set up camp in the hills. Shortage of food has even prompted him to kill, cook and eat, Ramona – the fat lady of his traveling show. Hex tells Cross that the Apaches are going to see his campfire and come looking for him. Then they will take their time in torturing and slaughtering him. Williams orders Wild Bill to finish Jonah off, but Hex outmaneuvers the zombie and blasts the cap of Hickok's skull clean off. Williams begins to get scared, and pleads with Jonah to save him. Jonah shoots him once in each knee, and leaves him for the Apaches to find.
name: Showdown

description:
The Justice League sees Guy Gardner murder a villian, Blake right in front of them and leave. When he comes back the Justice League tries to bring him to Justice. When they get him it is reavealed that he is not thereal Guy Gardner.

Also in this issue Blue Beetle rebuilds Booster Golds costume. It is a lot more bulky than the old one that was damaged by Doomsday.

Meanwhile Ice's brother Ewald Olafsdotter has taken over their fathers kingdom and brings the Ancient Ones to life. Ice's mother is able to get away and contact the Justice League Europe for help.

Continued in Guy Gardner #15 - The trouble with Guys part II
name: The Trouble With Guys

description: Alaric, the warlord from the future, undoes the origins of all the JLI heroes, turning them into normal people with no memories of their true lives. But when time begins to unravel, they must band together with the help of the 'one true Green Lantern'...Guy Gardner?
name: Ordinary People

description: Part 1 of 2. When a relief plane crashes in the deepest heart of an African jungle, the survivors are taken hostage by a tribe of female warriors. Only a League of women heroes will be allowed to contest for the captives' freedom...led by the Martian Manhunter, who uses his shape-shifting powers as never before!
name: Valley of the Daals

description: In "God's Tick," the Kid, Willie and Pathos visit Cristabel on her 18th birthday and attempt to understand the logic of the insane by seeing for themselves what insanity looks like.
name: God's Tick

description: The critically acclaimed miniseries concludes as Myrwann decides whether it is time to give up his immortality, but not before he determines whether his surrogate family can survive without him.
name: You and I

description:
The Legionnaires investigate the mysterious Kid Quantum as sparks fly between several Legionnaires.

While some Legionnaires find trouble in space in the form of illusionary loved ones, other Legionnaires try to quell a riot on Earth.
name: Skin Deep

description: The Metal Men take back their own lives while Mercury steals the newest Metal Man from their enemies. And the villains behind their recent tragedies stand revealed as...the Missile Men!
name: Metalurgency

description:
Robin takes on the Speedboyz--that is if he can convince Shotgun Smith he isn't one of them himself! Meanwhile, at Blackgate prison, the Cluemaster begins to make his escape!

At Blackgate, some of the prisoners (led by Arthur Brown, The Cluemaster) hypnotized their psychiatrist into bringing them weapons.

Robin unable to explain to Shotgun that he is not one of the Speedboyz, so he makes a quick escape. Robin tracks down and defeats the Speedboyz. Tells Shotgun where he can round them up. He left them for the sheriff. The prisoners escaped Blackgate and headed to Gotham City.
name: Busted!

description: Wesley Dodds's dark dreams grow more intense, drawing the Golden Age Sandman into a complex conspiracy involving child abuse and boxing scams.
name: The Brute: Act One

description:
The final chapter of "World's End!" The travelers of the World's End tavern share one last tale and head to the windows to watch as the reality storm comes to a close...

The time storm ends, and almost everyone of the guests leave. We also see almost all of the Family of endless, walking as great figures in the sky, but we do not get to know why.

Dream does not appear in this issue except on the cover.

Pencillers:

  • Bryan Talbot, pgs 1-9, 20-24
  • Gary Amaro, pgs 10-19

Inkers:

  • Mark Buckingham, pgs 1-3
  • Dick Giordano, pgs 4-8, 20-22
  • Bryan Talbot, pg 9
  • Tony Harris, pgs 10-19
  • Steve Leialoha, pgs 23-24
name: Worlds' End, Part 6

description: Part 1 of the 3-part 'History Lesson.' HELLBLAZER's John Constantine checks into Hotel Shade to help the Changing Man, Lenny and Kathy with their most harrowing guest - the History Man, who has the power to make time cartwheel backwards at a feverish pace. Plus, Kathy ponders her options when she discovers she's pregnant.
name: History Lesson, Part One: Pregnant for the First Time

description: Part 3 of 5. Kirk and Sulu once again travel through time to save the life of history's bloodiest tyrant...one who atrocities may now include the deaths of the two Starfleet officers.
name: Time Crime Part Three: Time...To Time!

description: Data and Judge Louvois stand trial for murder under an alien system of justice in which no known defense is admissible!
name: The Good Of The Many

description: An era ends as Swamp Thing, Lady Jane and John Constantine face Arcane in the epic conclusion to the Sunderland saga. But even if the Earth Elemental survives, his carefully-constructed private world may be shattered forever.
name: And in the End...

description: Part 2 of the 6-part “D.O.A.” Valor's condition continues to worsen as he returns to his native Daxam in search of answers, only to find that a terrible plague has struck the planet…and his mother may be its next victim.
name: D.O.A. Capter Two Future Shock
And Then She Fell to Earth

description: Good: Having a teleporter on the team. Not so good: The teleportation leads through a monster infested realm. Getting somewhere quick might be more dangerous then what awaits!
name: Steppin' Out

description: Jason Wynn, and major Vale, observe three soldiers attempting to leave Simmonsvile (A little hell on earth) in one piece. Meanwhile spawn is rethinking his life, when one of his homeless friends is attacked. Spawn brutally beats the attackers, and leaves to find answers to some of his very troubling questions. Spawn goes to dig up his own grave! Meanwhile Jason Wynn is in mid-exercise when he is transported to an angel station. He left a Man, he'll come back an Anti-Spawn!
name: Reflections Pt. 1
The Final Fury

volume.name: Captain Sternn: Running Out of Time

description:
events in Exiles #4 immediately precede this issue

A phenomena occurs across the world where people are trying to reach the highest point possible to reach the moon, regardless of a risk of death. A young woman with ultra abilities hovers over Los Angeles, radiating increasingly different waves of light and many believe she is the source of the people going mad. Doctor Deming, a survivor of the blast on Stronghold Island, is a patient in a hospital, bandaged from head to toe. A man named Doctor Rains, who is actually an agent of Aladdin, informs Doctor Deming that the woman above Los Angeles is Amber Hunt and demands answers, knowing she was involved with the Exiles. "Doctor Rains" gives the information that Doctor Deming gave him to Aladdin and they come to a plan that perhaps Spectral of the Strangers could shed some light on the situation with Amber Hunt, since his powers are also based on light. Aladdin also sends Wrath, an ultra, to handle this particular situation. The Pentagon decides to send Prime, who is armored with a special suit that could allow him to survive in space, to the moon to figure out what activity may be going on there. The Strangers arrive and quickly come to the conclusion that they should contact Amber directly. The Strangers are joined by Mantra and then are soon attacked by the combined might of Quattro and the Omega Team, who were sent by Rex Mundi. The Alternate sends the Solution, Hardcase and Choice to to help even the odds. Prototype is also sent to investigate the situation and joins the fight. Soon, Quattro and the Omega Team are defeated but are still able to escape in a spacecraft. The gathered heroes learn that the thing behind everything is on the moon, so they all decide to go to figure things out once and for all.
name: Part One
The Monster That Ate New York

description: Firearm battles cannibal super-beings in order to save the life of an innocent woman.
name: American Pastimes Part 4: Break-Thru

description: The well-meaning vigilante Night Man endangers the team due to the persuasive efforts of a villain with his own reasons for targeting the kids.

Hardcase introduces Choice to his secretary, agent and lawyer, hoping they will be able to help Choice by figuring out her past. Soon after that meeting, Hardcase and Choice go to another meeting with the Alternate, who informs them about the source of all ultra's powers and how the source is on the moon. Meanwhile, NM-E continues to stabilize himself and make himself stronger by assimilating any material that comes in handy, preferring organic material. The Alternate also reveals to Hardcase that the person behind the attack that killed the Squad, and the creator of NM-E, is Rex Mundi. The Alternate coerces Hardcase to go to the moon to get the source of power. Rex Mundi is also making plants of his own to secure the source of energy on the moon by sending the members of the Omega Team and Quattro. Hardcase and Choice are introduced by the Alternate to the members of the Solution, who will be joining them in the mission to the moon. Hardcase and Choice return to Hardcase's house when he sees an giant explosion occur on an island in the ocean, which is told in the pages of Exiles #4. The explosion creates a tidal wave that strikes against the shores of California. Hardcase and Choice try to save as many people as they can, but most of the attempt is futile as the tidal wave strikes quickly. The Alternate arrives to tell them that the explosion had something to do with events involving the moon, so they go to the space craft quickly.
name: Break-Thru: Sudden Surprises
